The entire family of the Copyright Society of Nigeria (COSON) mourns the demise of Chris Mba. Until his death, Mba was a frontline musician and staunch member of the Copyright Society of Nigeria (COSON), Nigeria’s biggest copyright Collective Management Organisation (CMO). Chris Mba reportedly died at the Lagos University Teaching Hospital (LUTH) on Wednesday, May 3, 2023. Chief Tony Okoroji, COSON chairman, described the late pop star as ” a great musician, whose contribution to repositioning the Highlife sound is unquestionable.” He added that “I am beyond sad at the loss of my colleague and friend, Chris Mba, “Not too long ago, I visited Chris at his Surulere home with the great Richard Cole, my colleague on the COSON Board. We went to share camaraderie with him despite his ill health and offer whatever support we could. “His death is devastating but we are consoled by the fact that as a great artiste, he left great recordings which we continue to sing and dance to. Our heartfelt condolences go to his family, friends and numerous fans”